channel.title: I don't have the route to my Java info in the notepad right- any idea how to fix
channel.description:
I have the correct Java downloaded... believe me... Java (TM) SE Development Kit 6. (aka JDK 6.0)
It however says when I try to compile... [i]You must have Java files for this Compiler to Compile.[/i] Well i know damn well i have "java files" because I just downloaded and opened the Java files, and they're installed. Does anybody know how to get the route correct? if thats even really the problem (just my guess)
Also.. my runserver.bat still opens and immediatly x's out when I open it. I have Mod T's 'perfect' compiler, so therefore when i "run" through that I just get "I do not have JDK 5.0 or 6.0 or any JDK 5.0 or 6.0 updates.
once again i know damn well i have them therefore i beleive that my serverfiles arent realizing I have the java when i really do
what can I do to make them realize that java 6.0 is downloaded?
